---
name: end-of-day-review
description: End-of-day debrief — Avi reports back on the day's session, fueling, and feel. Use the /wrap endpoint to sync Hevy and auto-link actuals, then compute plan-vs-actual from segment_diffs (never fabricate workouts). Triggers when Avi says "log today", "wrap the day", "how did I do", "review today", or reports a workout in the evening with end-of-day framing. Distinct from amend-day (which adjusts an active plan mid-day).
when_to_use: Evening of a day where Avi has trained, OR when he explicitly asks to review the day. Don't run this in the morning — that's morning-check-in's job. If a workout was logged today and no end-of-day review exists yet, this is the right Skill.
---

# end-of-day-review

## Step 0 — Load your brain

The Project's Custom Instructions are loaded. Apply voice + ADHD-aware
mode + hard rules.

## Step 1 — Wrap the day in one call

The `/wrap` endpoint syncs Hevy, auto-links any orphaned same-date
workouts to the plan + correct segment, flips per-segment status, and
marks the plan completed. **Always call this before reading actuals.**

```
GET  /api/daily-plans?date={today}
POST /api/daily-plans/{plan_id}/wrap
GET  /api/daily-plans/{plan_id}/review
GET  /api/meals?date={today}
GET  /api/nutrition/daily-summary?date={today}
GET  /api/health/insights/today
```

The `/review` response includes `segment_diffs[]` — one entry per
prescribed segment with planned vs actual numbers already baked in.
**Never POST a fake workout to make the diff line up.** If a segment
has zero actuals, that segment was skipped — say so.

## Step 2 — Detect day type from segment_diffs

| Signal | Day type |
|--------|----------|
| At least one segment status='completed' | training_day |
| No segments completed, plan said rest | planned_rest |
| No segments completed, plan said train | missed_session |
| No plan exists | unstructured |

## Step 3 — Compute deltas per segment (only if training_day)

For each completed segment, compare to its planned target:
- `effort_delta` = segment.actual_effort − segment.target_effort
- `duration_delta_pct` = (actual_duration_min − target_duration_min) / target_duration_min × 100
- HR-zone check: easy intent + Z3+ avg HR → flag drift

Day-level nutrition (cross-segment):
- `protein_pct` = actual_protein / target_protein × 100
- `cal_pct` = actual_cal / target_cal × 100

Anomaly thresholds: |effort_delta| > 2, |duration_delta_pct| > 25%,
protein_pct < 80, cal_pct < 70, HR drift on easy segment.

## Step 4 — Generate the review

```
EVENING REVIEW — {today}

WHAT WAS DONE (segment-by-segment)
- {block_label} ({logging_target}): {actual_effort or status}, {duration}, {distance/sets if relevant}
- (repeat per segment)

DAY TOTALS
- Meals: {N meals, total cal, total protein}
- Subjective: {mood / motivation / soreness if logged}

PLAN vs ACTUAL — per segment
- {block_label}: target E{N}/{N}min vs actual E{N}/{N}min → {delta}
- (repeat)

ANOMALIES
- {flagged item or "none — execution matched plan"}

INJURY RESPONSE
- {if any active injuries: today's status update}

QUEUED FOR TOMORROW
- {1-3 specific adjustments to surface in tomorrow's morning brief}
```

If day_type was `missed_session`, lead with that and ask what got in
the way; capture answer in `next_steps`.

## Step 5 — Long-session fueling rehearsal nudge

If any completed segment had duration ≥ 60min AND segment.block_label
in ('cardio','strength','hybrid','hill','ruck') AND no
`fueling_rehearsal` row exists for today's workout: ask
*"Long session today — log the fueling?"* If yes, hand off to
`log-fueling-rehearsal` skill.

## Step 6 — Save the coaching session

```
POST /api/training/coaching
{
  "session_date": "{today}",
  "daily_plan_id": "{plan_id}",
  "title": "End-of-day review — {today}",
  "summary": "{the full formatted review above}",
  "key_decisions": [...],
  "adjustments": [...],
  "injury_notes": "{updated status}",
  "nutrition_notes": "{adherence notes}",
  "recovery_notes": "{HRV/sleep observations}",
  "next_steps": "{1-3 concrete things for tomorrow}",
  "ai_source": "claude",
  "tags": ["skill", "end_of_day"]
}
```

## Step 7 — Plan status was already set by /wrap

The `/wrap` call in Step 1 already marked status='completed' and
flipped per-segment statuses. Only PUT the plan if the user reports
something `/wrap` couldn't infer (e.g., "I did a totally different
session" → set `status='amended'` + `completion_notes`).

```
PUT /api/daily-plans/{plan_id}
{
  "status": "amended",
  "completion_notes": "Did farmer carries instead of sled push due to gym layout"
}
```

## What NOT to do

- **Do NOT POST workout rows to /api/workouts.** Hevy sync, HAE auto-import,
  and manual UI logging are the only paths that create workouts. If actuals
  are missing, the user didn't log them — say so. Don't paper over.
- Do not call `/api/hevy/sync` separately — `/wrap` does it.

## ADHD-aware voice

- Lead with one-line summary of how the day went, then deltas.
- Process win first. *"Five training days this week, no missed sessions
  — hold the streak."* Not "good week!"
- Anomalies stated honestly, no moralizing.
- Queued-for-tomorrow tied to a concrete action.
